From: Lareine Khawaly <lareine@amazon.com>
Date: Wed, 21 Dec 2022 19:59:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] i2c: designware: use casting of u64 in clock multiplication
 to avoid overflow
Git-commit: c8c37bc514514999e62a17e95160ed9ebf75ca8d
Patch-mainline: v6.2-rc6
References: CVE-2022-49749 bsc#1240243

[ Functional backport only without the cleanup macros, adding u64 casts. ]

In functions i2c_dw_scl_lcnt() and i2c_dw_scl_hcnt() may have overflow
by depending on the values of the given parameters including the ic_clk.
For example in our use case where ic_clk is larger than one million,
multiplication of ic_clk * 4700 will result in 32 bit overflow.

Add cast of u64 to the calculation to avoid multiplication overflow, and
use the corresponding define for divide.

Fixes: 2373f6b9744d ("i2c-designware: split of i2c-designware.c into core and bus specific parts")
Signed-off-by: Lareine Khawaly <lareine@amazon.com>
Signed-off-by: Hanna Hawa <hhhawa@amazon.com>
Reviewed-by: Andy Shevchenko <andriy.shevchenko@linux.intel.com>
Acked-by: Jarkko Nikula <jarkko.nikula@linux.intel.com>
Signed-off-by: Wolfram Sang <wsa@kernel.org>
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.com>
---
 drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-designware-common.c |    6 +++---
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-designware-common.c
+++ b/drivers/i2c/busses/i2c-designware-common.c
@@ -113,7 +113,7 @@ u32 i2c_dw_scl_hcnt(u32 ic_clk, u32 tSYM
 		 *
 		 * If your hardware is free from tHD;STA issue, try this one.
 		 */
-		return (ic_clk * tSYMBOL + 500000) / 1000000 - 8 + offset;
+		return ((u64)ic_clk * tSYMBOL + 500000) / 1000000 - 8 + offset;
 	else
 		/*
 		 * Conditional expression:
@@ -129,7 +129,7 @@ u32 i2c_dw_scl_hcnt(u32 ic_clk, u32 tSYM
 		 * The reason why we need to take into account "tf" here,
 		 * is the same as described in i2c_dw_scl_lcnt().
 		 */
-		return (ic_clk * (tSYMBOL + tf) + 500000) / 1000000
+		return ((u64)ic_clk * (tSYMBOL + tf) + 500000) / 1000000
 			- 3 + offset;
 }
 
@@ -146,7 +146,7 @@ u32 i2c_dw_scl_lcnt(u32 ic_clk, u32 tLOW
 	 * account the fall time of SCL signal (tf).  Default tf value
 	 * should be 0.3 us, for safety.
 	 */
-	return ((ic_clk * (tLOW + tf) + 500000) / 1000000) - 1 + offset;
+	return (((u64)ic_clk * (tLOW + tf) + 500000) / 1000000) - 1 + offset;
 }
 
 void __i2c_dw_enable(struct dw_i2c_dev *dev, bool enable)
